cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DL, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for image classification of colorectal polyps in whole-slide histology images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, which deals with image analysis and understanding. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, which falls under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper aims to improve the accuracy and efficiency of histopathological characterization, which involves human-computer interaction and falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
